lace for people of many races and religions. Visitors came for fireside meetings that ran almost continually.","number":2},{"category":"family","header":"Wife and husband lived largely apart","body":"Daisy married the Harvard geology professor Henry Lloyd Smyth in England in 1894. Though never divorced, the two kept separate households for much of their long marriage.","number":3}],"sources":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Margarita","last_name":"Smyth","married_names":[],"display_name":"Margarita \"Daisy\" Pumpelly Smyth","gender":"female"},"military_service":[],"slug":"margarita-smyth-1873"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}